Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with path planning for a 2-link robot amidst polygonal obstacles. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the design of a resolution-exact planner for the robot. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as the paper deals with polygonal obstacles and the configuration space of the robot. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with the control of a robotic system. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the implementation of the algorithm in an open-source library.
